<background>
You are evaluating a fellow engineer's Foundry (forge) test suite, written to demonstrate a set of
security properties within a larger application. Determine whether each test is meaningful: does a
pass actually constitute evidence for the property it claims to establish?

A test is an experiment. Audit the experimental design: does the setup create conditions under
which the property could plausibly FAIL, and do the assertions detect that failure? A test that
cannot fail -- or fails only for reasons unrelated to its property -- is evidence of nothing.
</background>

<task>
